article.headline: Idaho 60, Long Beach State 56
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Dwayne Williams and Tanoris Shepard scored 16 points apiece and Idaho beat Long Beach State 60-56 Saturday. Williams had four 3-pointers and Shepard made seven of eight free throws. Rashaad Powell chipped in with 12 points, seven rebounds and four steals. Idaho climbed from an 11-point second half hole with late-game runs of 12-2 and 8-0. Idaho also hit 17 of 22 free throws, while Long Beach State was 11-for-19 from the foul line. The Vandals (13-14, 9-8 Big West Conference) have won four of their last five. The 49ers(6-19, 4-12) have lost eight in a row. Long Beach State took a 44-33 lead with 12:34 left in the game after Cody Pearson's dunk capped a 20-2 stretch. But Idaho soon went on the 12-2 run and eventually tied the game at 47-47 on two Shepard free throws with 6:09 remaining. Powell then scored seven points during the late 8-0 run. Kevin Roberts led the 49ers with 15 points. Jibril Hodges and Lucian Graham had 10 points apiece.
